To make our jumbled-up table look more

time to the stylesheet and clicking the refresh

Makes all the text inside the table smaller. The value is entered as a
percentage of the font size on the rest of the page.
Makes the table cover the full width of the body area.
Adds a 1-pixel-wide, solid, black border to each
element in the table. Notice that each element has its own separate
border. This is not the effect we’re looking for so we’ll fix that next.
